    • Method Detail

      • getSyntacticArgument

        public SyntacticArgument getSyntacticArgument()
        Returns the SyntacticArgument contained in this SynSemArgMap instance.
        Returns:
        the syntactic argument contained in this mapping or null if the syntactic argument is not set.

        Note that UBY-LMF requires the presence of a SyntacticArgument in every SynSemArgMap instance. Its absence may indicate to incomplete conversion of the original resource.

      • setSyntacticArgument

      • getSemanticArgument

        public SemanticArgument getSemanticArgument()
        Returns the SemanticArgument contained in this SynSemArgMap instance.
        Returns:
        the semantic argument contained in this mapping or null if the semantic argument is not set.

        Note that UBY-LMF requires the presence of a SemanticArgument in every SynSemArgMap instance. Its absence may indicate to incomplete conversion of the original resource.
